<item>
            <title>[SPARK-47385] Tuple encoder produces wrong results with Option inputs</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-47385</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The behavior of tupled encoders on the Option type was changed by &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/40755&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/40755&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;import&lt;/span&gt; org.apache.spark.sql.{Encoders, Encoder}&#160;

&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;case&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;class &lt;/span&gt;Required(name: &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt;)&#160;
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;case&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;class &lt;/span&gt;Optional(name: &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt;)&#160;

implicit val enc: Encoder[(Required, Option[Optional])] = Encoders.tuple(Encoders.product[Required], Encoders.product[Option[Optional]])&#160;
&#160;
spark.createDataFrame(Seq(&#160;
(Required(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;1&quot;&lt;/span&gt;), Some(Optional(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;1&quot;&lt;/span&gt;))),&#160;
(Required(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;2&quot;&lt;/span&gt;), None)&#160;
)).as[(Required, Option[Optional])].collect()&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Before the PR, the result is:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
Array((Required(1),Some(Optional(1))), (Required(2),None))&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;After the PR, the result is:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
Array((Required(1),Some(Optional(1))), (Required(2),&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;null&lt;/span&gt;)) &lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;which is incorrect because the original input is None rather than null.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
